summary: Eileen Gail Dinneen was an employee of the U.S. House of Representatives Select Committee on Assassinations (HSCA), also referred to as the Select Committee on Assassinations (SCAS). Payroll and certification reports from April to December 1978 document her employment, listing her position and salary. These documents provide administrative details, including her name and, in some instances, her social security number, indicating her role as a staff member during that period.
significance: Medium. Eileen Gail Dinneen's significance stems from her employment with the HSCA, as evidenced by multiple payroll and certification documents. While the documents confirm her employment, they do not specify her exact role or involvement in the committee's investigation, limiting her overall significance.
